Version 1.0  (Effective 1 August 2025)

PLEASE READ THIS AGREEMENT CAREFULLY. BY DOWNLOADING, INSTALLING, OR USING
ANY PART OF THE CYBERSAGE PLATFORM (THE “SOFTWARE”), YOU (“CUSTOMER”)
ACKNOWLEDGE THAT YOU HAVE AGREED TO BE BOUND BY ALL TERMS AND CONDITIONS OF
THIS END‑USER LICENSE AGREEMENT (“AGREEMENT”) WITH CYBERSAGE TECHNOLOGIES
(“CYBERSAGE”). IF YOU DO NOT AGREE, DO NOT INSTALL OR USE THE SOFTWARE.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
1. DEFINITIONS
   1.1 “Software” means the object‑code version of the Cybersage Platform
        module hosted in the repository `github.com/Orion-Intelligence/
        Orion-Intelligence`, together with all Updates supplied under this
        Agreement.
   1.2 “Authorized User” means an employee or contractor of Customer who
        has been granted access credentials and is bound by obligations
        no less restrictive than those herein.
   1.3 “License Key” means the technical means—file, token, or SaaS
        entitlement—furnished by Cybersage to enable the Software.
   1.4 “Updates” means bug fixes, patches, or enhancements Cybersage
        elects to provide under an active Support Subscription.

2. GRANT OF LICENSE
   2.1 Scope. Subject to full payment of applicable fees and Customer’s
        continued compliance, Cybersage grants Customer a limited,
        non‑exclusive, non‑transferable, non‑sublicensable license to
        install and use the Software solely:
        a) within Customer’s own internal production environment; and
        b) up to the quantity of License Keys purchased.
   2.2 Reservation of Rights. The Software is licensed, not sold. All
        rights not expressly granted are reserved by Cybersage.

3. RESTRICTIONS
   Customer shall not, and shall not permit any third‑party to:
   a) copy, modify, translate, or create derivative works of the Software;
   b) reverse‑engineer, decompile, or disassemble any part of the Software
      except to the limited extent such activity is expressly permitted by
      applicable law notwithstanding this restriction;
   c) remove or obscure any proprietary notices;
   d) disclose, sublicense, rent, lease, lend, supply as a service bureau,
      publish, or otherwise make the Software available to any third party.

4. CONFIDENTIALITY
   The Software, License Key, pricing, and non‑public documentation are
   “Confidential Information.” Customer shall maintain them in strict
   confidence, using at least the same degree of care as for its own
   confidential data, and in no event less than reasonable care.

5. OWNERSHIP
   Cybersage and its licensors retain all intellectual‑property rights
   in and to the Software and any copies thereof. No title passes to
   Customer under this Agreement.

6. LIMITED WARRANTY; DISCLAIMER
   6.1 Limited Warranty. Cybersage warrants that for ninety (90) days from
        first delivery the unmodified Software will substantially conform
        to its published documentation.
   6.2 Remedy. Cybersage’s sole liability and Customer’s exclusive remedy
        for breach of the foregoing warranty shall be, at Cybersage’s
        option, (a) repair or replacement of the non‑conforming Software
        or (b) refund of fees paid for the affected License Key.
   6.3 Disclaimer. EXCEPT AS EXPRESSLY PROVIDED, THE SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED
        “AS IS” AND CYBERSAGE DISCLAIMS ALL OTHER WARRANTIES, EXPRESS OR
        IMPLIED, INCLUDING WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A
        PARTICULAR PURPOSE, AND NON‑INFRINGEMENT.

7. LIMITATION OF LIABILITY
   IN NO EVENT SHALL CYBERSAGE BE LIABLE FOR ANY INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL,
   SPECIAL, CONSEQUENTIAL, OR PUNITIVE DAMAGES, OR FOR ANY LOSS OF
